[30;1m46 | [0m[35mSupported Shells[0m
[30;1m47 | [0m[35m================[0m
[30;1m48 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m49 | [0m[35mvirtualenvwrapper is a set of shell *functions* defined in Bourne[0m
[30;1m50 | [0m[35mshell compatible syntax.  It is tested under ``bash`` and[0m
[30;1m51 | [0m[35m``zsh``.  It may work with other shells, so if you find that it does[0m
[30;1m52 | [0m[35mwork with a shell not listed here please let us know by opening a[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m41[0m[34m of [0m[33m734[0m[31m ]--[0m
   Rule Id: [34mBD000702[0m
       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.DataExfiltration.Environment[0m

   Pattern: [32m(env|environment).{1,50}(get|post|curl|nc|invoke-restmethod)[0m
[30;1m19 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m20 | [0m[35m1.  Organizes all of your virtual environments in one place.[0m
[30;1m21 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m22 | [0m[35m2.  Wrappers for creating, copying and deleting environments, including[0m
[30;1m23 | [0m[35m    user-configurable hooks.[0m
[30;1m24 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m25 | [0m[35m3.  Use a single command to switch between environments.[0m

[30;1m5 | [0m[35m#################[0m
[30;1m6 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m7 | [0m[35mvirtualenvwrapper is a set of extensions to Ian Bicking's `virtualenv[0m
[30;1m8 | [0m[35m<http://pypi.python.org/pypi/virtualenv>`_ tool.  The extensions include[0m
[30;1m9 | [0m[35mwrappers for creating and deleting virtual environments and otherwise[0m
[30;1m10 | [0m[35mmanaging your development workflow, making it easier to work on more[0m
[30;1m11 | [0m[35mthan one project at a time without introducing conflicts in their[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m43[0m[34m of [0m[33m734[0m[31m ]--[0m
   Rule Id: [34mBD000702[0m
       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.DataExfiltration.Environment[0m

  Filename: [33m/virtualenvwrapper-6.1.1/docs/source/install.rst[0m
   Pattern: [32m(env|environment).{1,50}(get|post|curl|nc|invoke-restmethod)[0m
[30;1m161 | [0m[35m3. Run: ``mkvirtualenv temp``[0m
[30;1m162 | [0m[35m4. A new environment, ``temp`` is created and activated.[0m
[30;1m163 | [0m[35m5. Run: ``workon``[0m

[30;1m79 | [0m[35m================[0m
[30;1m80 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m81 | [0m[35mvirtualenvwrapper is a set of shell *functions* defined in Bourne[0m
[30;1m82 | [0m[35mshell compatible syntax.  It is tested under ``bash`` and[0m
[30;1m83 | [0m[35m``zsh``.  It may work with other shells, so if you find that it does[0m
[30;1m84 | [0m[35mwork with a shell not listed here please let us know by opening a[0m

[30;1m51 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m52 | [0m[35m1.  Organizes all of your virtual environments in one place.[0m
[30;1m53 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m54 | [0m[35m2.  Wrappers for creating, copying and deleting environments, including[0m
[30;1m55 | [0m[35m    user-configurable hooks.[0m
[30;1m56 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m57 | [0m[35m3.  Use a single command to switch between environments.[0m

[30;1m2 | [0m[35m Why virtualenvwrapper is (Mostly) Not Written In Python[0m
[30;1m3 | [0m[35m=========================================================[0m
[30;1m4 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m5 | [0m[35mIf you look at the source code for virtualenvwrapper you will see that[0m
[30;1m6 | [0m[35mmost of the interesting parts are implemented as shell functions in[0m
[30;1m7 | [0m[35m``virtualenvwrapper.sh``. The hook loader is a Python app, but doesn't[0m
[30;1m8 | [0m[35mdo much to manage the virtualenvs. Some of the most frequently asked[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m531[0m[34m of [0m[33m734[0m[31m ]--[0m
   Rule Id: [34mBD000610[0m
       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.LOLBAS.Linux[0m
  Severity: [36mModerate[0m, Confidence: [36mLow[0m
  Filename: [33m/virtualenvwrapper-6.1.1/docs/source/design.rst[0m
   Pattern: [32m\s(apt|apt\-get|aria2c|arp|ash|awk|base64|bash|bpftrace|busybox|cat|chmod|chown|cp|cpan|cpulimit|crontab|csh|curl|cut|dash|dd|diff|dmesg|dmsetup|dnf|docker|dpkg|easy_install|ed|emacs|env|expand|expect|facter|find|finger|flock|fmt|ftp|gawk|gdb|gimp|git|grep|head|iftop|ionice|ip|irb|jjs|journalctl|jrunscript|ksh|ld\.so|ldconfig|logsave|ltrace|lua|mail|mawk|mount|mtr|mv|mysql|nano|nawk|nc|nice|nl|nmap|node|od|openssl|perl|pg|php|pic|pico|pip|puppet|readelf|red|rlogin|rlwrap|rpm|rpmquery|rsync|ruby|run\-mailcap|run\-parts|rvim|scp|screen|script|sed|service|setarch|sftp|shuf|smbclient|socat|sort|sqlite3|ssh|start\-stop\-daemon|stdbuf|strace|systemctl|tail|tar|taskset|tclsh|tcpdump|tee|telnet|tftp|time|timeout|tmux|top|ul|unexpand|uniq|unshare|vi|vim|watch|wget|whois|wish|xargs|xxd|yum|zsh|zypper)\s[0m
[30;1m102 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m103 | [0m[35mSimply running ``bin/activate``, without using ``source`` doesn't work[0m
[30;1m104 | [0m[35mbecause it sets up the environment of the *child* process, without[0m
[30;1m105 | [0m[35maffecting the parent. In order to source the activate script in the[0m
[30;1m106 | [0m[35minteractive shell, both ``mkvirtualenv`` and ``workon`` also need to[0m
[30;1m107 | [0m[35mbe run in that shell process.[0m
[30;1m108 | [0m[35m[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m532[0m[34m of [0m[33m734[0m[31m ]--[0m
   Rule Id: [34mBD000610[0m
       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.LOLBAS.Linux[0m
  Severity: [36mModerate[0m, Confidence: [36mLow[0m
